# shadcn/ui Guidelines

## Component Installation

- Install components via CLI: `npx shadcn-ui@latest add [component]`
- Components are stored in `src/components/ui/`
- Always use the latest versions from shadcn/ui

## Essential Components for Dashboard

```bash
# Core UI components
npx shadcn-ui@latest add button
npx shadcn-ui@latest add input
npx shadcn-ui@latest add card
npx shadcn-ui@latest add table
npx shadcn-ui@latest add dialog
npx shadcn-ui@latest add form
npx shadcn-ui@latest add select
npx shadcn-ui@latest add badge
npx shadcn-ui@latest add avatar
npx shadcn-ui@latest add dropdown-menu
npx shadcn-ui@latest add navigation-menu
npx shadcn-ui@latest add tabs
npx shadcn-ui@latest add sheet
npx shadcn-ui@latest add toast
npx shadcn-ui@latest add alert
npx shadcn-ui@latest add progress
npx shadcn-ui@latest add calendar
npx shadcn-ui@latest add data-table
```

## Component Usage Patterns

### Forms

- Always use `react-hook-form` with `zod` validation
- Use shadcn/ui Form components for consistent styling
- Implement proper error handling and validation

```typescript
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import {
  Form,
  FormControl,
  FormField,
  FormItem,
  FormLabel,
  FormMessage,
} from "@/components/ui/form";
```

### Data Display

- Use `Table` component for data lists
- Use `Card` component for dashboard widgets
- Use `Badge` for status indicators
- Use `Avatar` for user profiles

### Navigation

- Use `NavigationMenu` for main navigation
- Use `Sheet` for mobile sidebar
- Use `DropdownMenu` for user menus

## Customization

- Modify `src/components/ui/` components as needed
- Use CSS variables for theming in `globals.css`
- Follow the design system color palette
- Maintain accessibility standards (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)

## Composition Patterns

- Create compound components using shadcn/ui primitives
- Use slot patterns for flexible component composition
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces for props

